FLW High Frequency Surveys

09 October 2020

West Bengal Survey Data

NOTE: All of the Ns in the graphs reflect the total number of ASHAs surveyed.

Symptom + Covid Trends

For each symptom, plotted the average number of cases that FLWs came across over the previous 3 days.

That is = Case counts reported by all FLWs surveyed on a particular day/# of FLWs surveyed on that day.

Note: We did not conduct any surveys from July 5-August 5.

1. Fever

2. Cough

3. Loss of smell

4. Covid toes

5. Confirmed coronavirus cases

FLW Symptoms

We also asked FLWs whether they themselves were experiencing any symptoms.

For each symptom, we have plotted the proportion of FLWs who mentioned they were experiencing this symptom, each survey day. That is: Total # of FLWs who mentioned experiencing the symptom/# of FLWs who were asked this question on that survey day.

Note: We did not conduct any surveys from July 5-August 5.

1. Fever

2. Cough

3. Loss of ability to smell/taste

4. Shortness of breath/difficulty breathing

Home visits, Equipment, Challenges Faced

Note: We did not conduct any surveys from July 5-August 5.

1. Proportion of homes visited

The below graph shows the average proportion of houses visited by FLWs (in the last 3 days), out of the total number of households that come under their jurisdiction.

We calculate the proportion of households visited by an FLW in the last 3 days as: # of households visited in last 3 days/total number of households in that FLWs jurisdiction.

We then plot the average of the above number, for all FLWs surveyed on a particular day.

2. Equipment

Number of FLWs who mentioned that they received various equipment.

2. Equipment given by government

Out of the equipment that FLWs have mentioned, the ones that were given to them by the government.

3. Challenges faced by FLWs

Number of FLWs who mentioned various challenges (without probing).

4. Challenges faced by FLWs

Number of FLWs who mentioned various challenges (without probing+ probed responses).

Immunization, Pregnant Women, TB Tests

Note: We did not conduct any surveys from July 5-August 5.

1. Children Vaccinated

The below graph shows count of children in the FLWs area that were vaccinated in the last 7 days.

We plot the average of the above number, for all FLWs surveyed on a particular day.

2. Vaccination Supply

The below graph shows the proportion of FLWs that reported having adequate supply of vaccines for the current month on a particular day.

3. Pregnant Women House Visits

The below graph shows the number of pregnant women visited by the FLW in the last 7 days.

We then plot the average of the above number, for all FLWs surveyed on a particular day.

4. TB Cough Tests

The below graph shows the number of people sent for a TB cough test by the FLW in the last 7 days.

We then plot the average of the above number, for all FLWs surveyed on a particular day.

Masks, Social Distancing

Note: We did not conduct any surveys from July 5-August 5.

1. Mask Usage

The below graph shows how many people (out of 100) in the FLWs area covered their nose and mouth with a mask/face covering when stepping out.

We then plot the average of the above number, for all FLWs surveyed on a particular day.

2. Public Gathering/Socializing

The below graph shows approximately how many people were seen in a public gathering place in the village (such as tea stalls, parks) in the last 2 days (yesterday and day before yesterday).

We then plot the average of the above number, for all FLWs surveyed on a particular day.
